From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [G8] JSON Schema robustness in Gemma 4 tool declarations

Targets: templates/gemma4/upstream/<size>.jinja — Google's 2026-07-09
template (big family `ae53464b`, small family `0a2c8073`). Applies cleanly
to all five sizes (12B-it, 26B-A4B-it, 31B-it, E2B-it, E4B-it); the
`format_parameters` macro is identical across them.

Status: OPT-IN. Gemma 4 ships no default `patched/` stack (G7/G9/G10 were
retired when Google fixed them upstream on 2026-07-09), so this patch is
applied only by users whose tools use the affected schema constructs.

Failure mode: Google's `format_parameters` only emits `enum` (and only when
`type == 'STRING'`) plus `items` for arrays. Every other JSON Schema
construct is **silently dropped** from the tool declaration the model sees:

  - `anyOf` / `oneOf` / `allOf`   (Optional[...] / union types)
  - `$ref` / `$defs`             (nested Pydantic models)
  - `const`
  - `enum` on a non-STRING type
  - union `type` arrays (e.g. `"type": ["string", "null"]`)

These are exactly what Pydantic v2 emits, so MCP tools generated from
Pydantic models lose their constraints — the model cannot see that a field
is optional, a reference, or restricted to a fixed value.

Fix: rewrite the per-property branch to collect `type` into a `type_names`
namespace (handling both string and list forms) and emit `anyOf` / `oneOf` /
`allOf` / `$ref` / `$defs` / `const` / `enum` explicitly, independent of the
declared type.

Verified against the 2026-07-09 upstream: a tool whose properties use
`anyOf`, `$ref`, and `const` renders all three in the patched output and
none of them in stock upstream.

Prior art: u/sigjhl's iterated template (r/LocalLLaMA), a superset of the
HF PR at `google/gemma-4-31B-it/discussions/91` (still unmerged as of
2026-07-20). Snapshotted at
docs/sources/pastebins/tBAHN6FV-sigjhl-gemma4-jsonschema-robustness.jinja.

Regenerated 2026-07-20 against the 2026-07-09 upstream. The previous
revision carried a 7th hunk that only added a trailing newline; Google's
new file already ends with one, so that hunk is dropped.

